Summer at its finest, friends. Load up your farmer's market totes and then come home and dump anything and everything onto a pan, roast it up, and toss it with some perfectly chewy pasta, roasted garlic, lemon juice, and a huge dollop of walnut pesto. Vegan, veggie-loaded, great hot or cold, and ready to be flexible for all your favorite things.⠀
⠀

node.text:
This little unicorn somehow manages to feel like a comfort food with its rich creamy sauce (thank you, coconut creeeaaam!) and tender chicken but still taste super bright, fresh, and summery, courtesy of the zippy lemongrass flavor and bunches of lime zest and fresh cilantro. It's all piled on top of some steamy rice with tender-crisp and golden brown little zucchinis (because hi, summer veg abundance). Yum yum yuuuum, we cannot stop with this.⠀
⠀
New on the blog! --> https://pinchofyum.com/lemongrass-chicken-with-rice-and-zucchini ⠀

node.text:
Yes YES, summer is for pasta! Especially this pasta. Wide, flat, beautiful pappardelle (oh thank you so, @delallofoods) twisting all around a bunch of summery produce like bursty cherry tomatoes, bright zucchini, and sweet crunchy fresh corn (but you can get creative with whatever garden goods you have.) A little luscious light cream sauce to hold it all together and then, AND THEN, the most perfect pan-fried chicken right alongside it all. Whoo, this one's a gem.⠀
⠀
Recipe #sponsored by @delallofoods

node.text:
If you have a couple of minutes to spare, we would love to explain to you how amazing this lemon sauce is. Like, in explicit detail. Like how it's super rich and creamy but still somehow light. The brightness of the lemon and the savory softness of the shallot. Any sauce that involves butter in this way is already perfect, but with hints of thyme and a pop of fresh herbs at the end...we would straight up drink it if we could. (There are also salmon fillets, roasty potatoes, and broccoli involved that are all v v good. But the sauce. THE SAUCE.)⠀
⠀
